headline: Palantir Hits New Peak as U.S. Defense Ties Fuel Rally
summary: Palantir Technologies (NASDAQ:PLTR) rose about 3% on Monday, reaching a record close of $141.4 and surpassing its prior high set Friday.  The gains came alongside a broader recovery in U.S. equities as investors monitored geopolitical risks tied to renewed tensions between Israel and Iran.  Analysts at Loop Capital raised their price target for Palantir to $155 last week, calling the stock a runaway freight train, well ahead of the average Wall Street estimate of $95, according to Visible Alpha.

summary: Palantir Technologies  stock just hit another record, but the lofty valuation of the defense-focused artificial-intelligence software company has analysts questioning whether it can go much higher.
